results.title: Australian diary. No. 126
results.creator_credit: Department of the Interior and R.J. Edwards
results.brief_description: Magazine items: Crop protection from the air. Use of aircraft for pasture improvement and pest control has been developed to a high state of efficiency, through the combined efforts of the farmer and the flier. Guide dogs bring freedom and new life to blind people. Shows them meeting and training with their new masters at the National Guide Dog Training Centre, Kew, Vic. Coal mines close but the people of Cessnock, N.S.W. work an “industrial miracle”.

results.title: Australian diary. No. 123
results.creator_credit: Dept of the Interior, Australian National Film Board and Jack S. Allan
results.brief_description: Magazine items: The giant telescope at Parkes, N.S.W. is the largest in the Southern Hemisphere. It is occupied with a fulltime research programme into radio astronomy. At Collaroy, Sydney, the Salvation Army has organized a unique Music Camp for children,from eight to fifteen years. University College of Townsville is the first in the state of Queensland outside Brisbane.
